        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 12:16PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 1216 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Stonewall, or 21 miles west of Trinidad, moving
northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Segundo and Weston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
